Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil @water{600%ml} in a #pot{} (or your kettle).

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces.

Chop the @potatoes{1} into small cubes (peeling optional).

Run a #peeler{} lengthways along the @courgette{1} to create thin ribbons (3 per person). Cut the remaining courgette into cubes.

== Sesame Seeds ==

Place a #pan{} over medium heat (without oil).

Once hot, add the @sesame seeds{1%sachet} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from pan and keep aside.

== Soup ==

Place a #medium pot{} over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Add the onion and fry until softened, ~{2%minutes}.

Add the courgette cubes and cook, stirring, for ~{3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch the sesame seeds like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Turn the heat to high and add the chopped potatoes, boiled water and @vegetable stock{1%sachet} to the pot and bring to a boil.

Cover and cook for ~{10%minutes} over medium-low heat.

Meanwhile, return your now empty pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Fry the courgette ribbons for ~{5%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Croutons ==

Roughly tear the @brioche buns{2} into 2cm chunks.

Pop onto a lined #baking tray{} then toss in a drizzle of @oil{to taste} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Warm in the oven until golden brown, ~{8-10%minutes}.

== Finishing ==

Remove the soup from the heat and blend until smooth.

Add a little extra @water{to taste} if the soup is too thick.

Stir in @green pesto{1%sachet} and season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the soup between your #bowls{}.

Top with the brioche croutons and crumble over the @goat's cheese{100%grams}.

Garnish with the courgette ribbons and sesame seeds.